
---

# ✅ Module 1 Quiz – Answer Key

| Question | Correct Answer                                                 | Explanation                                                            |
| -------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| 1        | **C** - A way for software applications to communicate         | This is the purpose of an API.                                         |
| 2        | **C** - A restaurant menu delivering food options              | The menu is the interface; you ask, and the kitchen (server) delivers. |
| 3        | **C** - GraphQL API                                            | GraphQL is an architecture type, not an access type.                   |
| 4        | **B** - Sends requests to the server                           | The client initiates communication by sending a request.               |
| 5        | **D** - JSON                                                   | JSON is lightweight and widely used for API data exchange.             |
| 6        | **C** - GET                                                    | The GET method retrieves data from the server.                         |
| 7        | **C** - Resource not found                                     | 404 indicates the requested resource is missing.                       |
| 8        | **C** - They allow apps to communicate and reuse functionality | APIs enable software systems to interact and extend features.          |
| 9        | **B** - A URL that represents a specific resource              | Endpoints are URL paths for specific API functions or data.            |
| 10       | **B** - HTTP methods like GET and POST                         | REST APIs use standard HTTP verbs to perform operations.               |

